    <div class="row">
      <div class="column">
        <div class="appdescription">
        <h2> Getting Started </h2>
        <h5> Sign up on the right. -------> </h5>
        <p>Tradr is a stock market simulation game where users are able to utilize realtime stock prices to experiment with various investment strategies.  Users are able to purchase shares of various companies, and track their return over time.  After purchasing shares, users are able to sell off a portion or all of their shares at any time.  In addition to the buy/sell functionality of the game, users are also able to 'follow' companies, to view a line graph of the past 100 day's pricing information. </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="column">
        <div class="authenticate">
          <div class="authenticate-header">
        <h2>Sign Up</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="authenticate-body">
        <%= form_for(resource, as: resource_name, url: registration_path(resource_name)) do |f| %>
        <%= render "devise/shared/error_messages", resource: resource %>

        <div class="field">
          <%= f.label :email %>
          <%= f.email_field :email, autofocus: true, autocomplete: "email" %>
        </div>

        <div class="field">
          <%= f.label :user_name, "User Name" %>
          <%= f.text_field :user_name, autofocus: true, autocomplete: "user_name" %>
        </div>

        <div class="field">
          <%= f.label :password %>
          <% if @minimum_password_length %>
          <em>(<%= @minimum_password_length %> characters minimum)</em>
          <% end %><br />
          <%= f.password_field :password, autocomplete: "new-password" %>
        </div>

        <div class="field">
          <%= f.label :password_confirmation %>
          <%= f.password_field :password_confirmation, autocomplete: "new-password" %>
        </div>

        <div class="actions">
          <%= f.submit "Sign up" %> <br />
          <% end %>
          <%= render "devise/shared/links" %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
